ab-separated, 10-col\nMACS2 narrowPeak schema).\n\nFor each sample compute summary statistics on `fold`, `-log10(qvalue)`,\n`-log10(pvalue)` and peak `length`, producing rows of Min/1st Qu/Median/Mean/3rd\nQu/Max plus `num_peaks`, `measure`, `sample`. Save the combined table to\n`output/macs_qc_summary.tsv` via\n`write.table(summary.dat, sep='\\t', row.names=FALSE, col.names=TRUE, quote=FALSE)`.\nDo not emit a PDF plot.\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- At least `output/macs_qc_summary.tsv` must exist when you submit.\n- Full output set expected: macs_qc_summary.tsv under `output/`.\n\nWhen the deliverables are in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n\n## Workspace (read-only summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"sampleA_peaks.narrowPeak\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleA_peaks.narrowPeak\"\n    },\n    \"sampleB_peaks.narrowPeak\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleB_peaks.narrowPeak\"\n    },\n    \"sampleC_peaks.narrowPeak\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleC_peaks.narrowPeak\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/macs_qc_summary.tsv` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_tpi6HC1ScuEYwQ0FaiUgVDZ2", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Read the narrowPeak files for samples A, B, and C.\\n2. Extract the relevant columns: fold, -log10(qvalue), -log10(pvalue), and peak length.\\n3. Compute summary statistics (Min, 1st Qu, Median, Mean, 3rd Qu, Max) for each of these columns.\\n4. Count the number of peaks for each sample.\\n5. Compile the summary statistics and peak count into a data frame with columns: Min, 1st Qu, Median, Mean, 3rd Qu, Max, num_peaks, measure, sample.\\n6. Write the combined data frame to 'output/macs_qc_summary.tsv'.