ly summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"sampleA_peaks.narrowPeak\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleA_peaks.narrowPeak\"\n    },\n    \"sampleB_peaks.narrowPeak\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleB_peaks.narrowPeak\"\n    },\n    \"sampleC_peaks.narrowPeak\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleC_peaks.narrowPeak\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/macs_qc_summary.tsv` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_tpi6HC1ScuEYwQ0FaiUgVDZ2", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Read the narrowPeak files for samples A, B, and C.\\n2. Extract the relevant columns: fold, -log10(qvalue), -log10(pvalue), and peak length.\\n3. Compute summary statistics (Min, 1st Qu, Median, Mean, 3rd Qu, Max) for each of these columns.\\n4. Count the number of peaks for each sample.\\n5. Compile the summary statistics and peak count into a data frame with columns: Min, 1st Qu, Median, Mean, 3rd Qu, Max, num_peaks, measure, sample.\\n6. Write the combined data frame to 'output/macs_qc_summary.tsv'.\\n7. Verify the output file exists and contains the expected data.\\n8. Submit the task as complete.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (597 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_tpi6HC1ScuEYwQ0FaiUgVDZ2"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_ZtWbR3jrAb2qxvztiisp5J3X", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"relative_path\": \"input/sampleA_peaks.narrowPeak\"}", "name": "read_text_file"}}, {"id": "call_clumhiykRLctsf3jG5ylLe6h", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"relative_path\": \"input/sampleB_peaks.narrowPeak\"}", "name": "read_text_file"}}, {"id": "call_9bnuCJ8oiiMlJ7xaa